longBusinessSummary: First Nordic Metals Corp., an exploration stage company, engages in the acquisition, exploration, and evaluation of mineral properties in Sweden and Finland. The company explores for iron ore, gold, silver, copper, and zinc deposits. Its flagship project is the 45% Barsele Gold Project that covers an area of approximately 47,000 hectares located in Västerbottens Län, northern Sweden. The company was formerly known as Barsele Minerals Corp. and changed its name to First Nordic Metals Corp. in March 2024. First Nordic Metals Corp. was incorporated in 2013 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
